Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new coding scheme for distributed storage systems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the construction of codes for efficient data storage and retrieval. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the proposed codes can be used in networked storage systems. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with distributed storage systems that can be modeled as networks. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a less likely category, but the paper may involve some analysis of the computational complexity of the proposed codes.
